              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four 5-mm-thick Li-drifted silicon detectors.",
                "The spin orientation of the beam was alternated",
                "frequently during a run at a given setting and the",
                "resulting spectra were routed into a pulse-height",
                "analyzer operating in a 8 x 128 mode.",
                "Four counting arrangements were used:",
                " (1) At angles forward of 20 degr. strip targets",
                "     2 mm wide and normal to the beam were used,",
                " (2) At angles between 20 and 60 degr., foil targets",
                "     were used normal to the beam;",
                " (3) At angles between 60 and 125 degr., foil targets",
                "     were used on a transmission setting;",
                " (4) At angles between 120 and 165 degr., foil targets",
                "     were used on a reflection setting."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two NaI scintillation counters placed above",
                "the scattering plane at angles of +-18 degr.relative",
                "to the beam axis were used to monitor the beam position",
                "on the target.",
                "The beam polarization was monitored continuously both",
                "at the exit of the accelerator, using the sampling",
                "polarimeter."
              ]
            }
          ],
